	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85776><span id=Sage>Cannis of the Seven Seas</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>690 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.35]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok I understand where your coming from now but I was going by your level. You have SoW so there is no need to snare pull once you have SoW. I hunted in Frontier Mountain, Overthere, Eastern Wastes and Dreadlands from 28th-45th respectively, these all being outdoor zones so I was designated puller. I found that the faster you pull the more the group wanted you. I would leave to pull at 1 bub from the mobs death to get another but if you have 4 groups in area pullin mobs tend to thin out quickly along with ks that can occur from a long pull.&nbsp;&nbsp;So my point is that snare is not a good way to pull post 30. You will be pulling from distances in those zones.<br><br>Once you get in Overthere, Dreadlands group you will find what the group demands of a chain puller.  As far as tank pulling agro you will find as I did that takes a while for the tank to build up enough agro to keep the mob off you its not so bad at lower levels but at higher levels pulling mob agro off you will get harder for tanks.  (CoM comes to mind here 49sk 51 monk and 45 rogue and me 42 ranger...Ranger gets beat down harmony/snare pulling...CH for Ranger CH for Ranger CH for ranger) I am of the belief that you form your habits early, I use to snare at beginnings or middle of fights and have moved to end of fight due to damage inflicted on me till tank could build agro.<br><br>Trust me on this one, your world is going to change radically over the next few levels. This where the techniques of agro control start to come into play.<br><br>As for kiting multiple adds I was assuming outdoor scenario with no enchanter and assuming more than one add. For 1-2 adds ghetto mez is perfectly viable way to take care of them its just when you have more than that I found kiting away from group is best for me, easy to do with SoW (practice archery) you can keep agro at will (flamelick/snare)and if things go bad the group can escape. The point being is that your group lives even if you do not, making ranger look like hero...therefore increasing our public image...which leads to /ooc Group looking for Ranger levels 30-35.<br><br>If I came across as attacking your post I apologize I sometimes don't state things in the most diplomatic way. I will try to do better in the future.</p>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 65th Ranger<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69645" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69645</a> <br><br></td></tr>
